{"id": "EUVD-2025-5245", "enisaUuid": "313cda27-5797-374f-8c0e-5133dc625ea3", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nOPP: add index check to assert to avoid buffer overflow in _read_freq()\n\nPass the freq index to the assert function to make sure\nwe do not read a freq out of the opp->rates[] table when called\nfrom the indexed variants:\ndev_pm_opp_find_freq_exact_indexed() or\ndev_pm_opp_find_freq_ceil/floor_indexed().\n\nAdd a secondary parameter to the assert function, unused\nfor assert_single_clk() then add assert_clk_index() which\nwill check for the clock index when called from the _indexed()\nfind functions.", "datePublished": "2025-02-27T02:07:17", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-03T19:33:10", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2024-57998", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/774dd6f0f0a61c9c3848e025d7d9eeed1a7ca4cd", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/7d68c20638e50d5eb4576492a7958328ae445248", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/d659bc68ed489022ea33342cfbda2911a81e7a0d", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/da2a6acc73933b7812c94794726e438cde39e037", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/eb6ffa0192ba83ece1a318b956265519c5c7dcec", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/03/msg00028.html"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-57998", "GHSA-f86f-gm48-j2g3"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.04, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "18ffad3c-6f35-3ca6-a8ff-1693993b3b95", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "92fcb46659d5dbfdad0422a503e289085990a5d0 <774dd6f0f0a61c9c3848e025d7d9eeed1a7ca4cd"}, {"id": "2d587058-7839-3916-8f1b-f5ace0a2aab4", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.13.2"}, {"id": "510ce617-dff9-30c7-9285-26e41693847e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "142e17c1c2b48e3fb4f024e62ab6dee18f268694 <eb6ffa0192ba83ece1a318b956265519c5c7dcec"}, {"id": "5c03a1f7-c9fa-3c71-adbe-f90a00c27470", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "142e17c1c2b48e3fb4f024e62a